seal     : A language model never reads letters. The first thing that happens to your text is that it is cut into tokens — sub-word pieces drawn from a fixed vocabulary. Common words are a single token; rare words shatter into several; even the space before a word is part of it. Before meaning, before prediction, there is the cut.
